The paper proposes a new language for defining information-extractors from textual content based on the document spanners framework. This involves processing and analyzing text data, which falls under the categories of databases (cs.DB), computational linguistics (cs.CL), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
